## Description {#details}

Interfaces for registering analysis passes, producing common pass manager configurations, and parsing of pass pipelines.

<Link id="l00237" /><CodeLine lineNumber="237"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// build them.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00310" /><CodeLine lineNumber="310"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00311" /><CodeLine lineNumber="311"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Parse a textual pass pipeline description into a \\c</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00312" /><CodeLine lineNumber="312"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// ModulePassManager.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00313" /><CodeLine lineNumber="313"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00314" /><CodeLine lineNumber="314"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// The format of the textual pass pipeline description looks something like:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00315" /><CodeLine lineNumber="315"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00316" /><CodeLine lineNumber="316"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   module(function(instcombine,sroa),dce,cgscc(inliner,function(...)),...)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00317" /><CodeLine lineNumber="317"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00318" /><CodeLine lineNumber="318"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Pass managers have ()s describing the nest structure of passes. All passes</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00319" /><CodeLine lineNumber="319"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// are comma separated. As a special shortcut, if the very first pass is not</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00320" /><CodeLine lineNumber="320"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// a module pass (as a module pass manager is), this will automatically form</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00321" /><CodeLine lineNumber="321"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// the shortest stack of pass managers that allow inserting that first pass.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00322" /><CodeLine lineNumber="322"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// So, assuming function passes &#39;fpassN&#39;, CGSCC passes &#39;cgpassN&#39;, and loop</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00323" /><CodeLine lineNumber="323"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// passes &#39;lpassN&#39;, all of these are valid:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00324" /><CodeLine lineNumber="324"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00325" /><CodeLine lineNumber="325"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   fpass1,fpass2,fpass3</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00326" /><CodeLine lineNumber="326"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   cgpass1,cgpass2,cgpass3</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00327" /><CodeLine lineNumber="327"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   lpass1,lpass2,lpass3</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00328" /><CodeLine lineNumber="328"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00329" /><CodeLine lineNumber="329"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// And they are equivalent to the following (resp.):</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00330" /><CodeLine lineNumber="330"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00331" /><CodeLine lineNumber="331"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   module(function(fpass1,fpass2,fpass3))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00332" /><CodeLine lineNumber="332"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   module(cgscc(cgpass1,cgpass2,cgpass3))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00333" /><CodeLine lineNumber="333"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   module(function(loop(lpass1,lpass2,lpass3)))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00334" /><CodeLine lineNumber="334"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00335" /><CodeLine lineNumber="335"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// This shortcut is especially useful for debugging and testing small pass</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00336" /><CodeLine lineNumber="336"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// combinations.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00337" /><CodeLine lineNumber="337"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00338" /><CodeLine lineNumber="338"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// The sequence of passes aren&#39;t necessarily the exact same kind of pass.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00339" /><CodeLine lineNumber="339"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// You can mix different levels implicitly if adaptor passes are defined to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00340" /><CodeLine lineNumber="340"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// make them work. For example,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00341" /><CodeLine lineNumber="341"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00342" /><CodeLine lineNumber="342"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   mpass1,fpass1,fpass2,mpass2,lpass1</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00343" /><CodeLine lineNumber="343"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00344" /><CodeLine lineNumber="344"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// This pipeline uses only one pass manager: the top-level module manager.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00345" /><CodeLine lineNumber="345"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// fpass1,fpass2 and lpass1 are added into the top-level module manager</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00346" /><CodeLine lineNumber="346"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// using only adaptor passes. No nested function/loop pass managers are</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00347" /><CodeLine lineNumber="347"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// added. The purpose is to allow easy pass testing when the user</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00348" /><CodeLine lineNumber="348"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// specifically want the pass to run under a adaptor directly. This is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00349" /><CodeLine lineNumber="349"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// preferred when a pipeline is largely of one type, but one or just a few</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00350" /><CodeLine lineNumber="350"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// passes are of different types(See PassBuilder.cpp for examples).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00351" /><CodeLine lineNumber="351"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/passbuilder/#a9ca0e57e6445ab2fe568e53ba29cc0fd">parsePassPipeline</a>(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a79ab9199d2ba6a1c9cac2b79efc194a3">ModulePassManager</a> &amp;MPM, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> PipelineText);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00352" /><CodeLine lineNumber="352"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00353" /><CodeLine lineNumber="353"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// &#123;&#123;@ Parse a textual pass pipeline description into a specific PassManager</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00354" /><CodeLine lineNumber="354"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00355" /><CodeLine lineNumber="355"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Automatic deduction of an appropriate pass manager stack is not supported.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00358" /><CodeLine lineNumber="358"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00359" /><CodeLine lineNumber="359"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   function(lpass)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00360" /><CodeLine lineNumber="360"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/passbuilder/#a9ca0e57e6445ab2fe568e53ba29cc0fd">parsePassPipeline</a>(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a4ded4558d2b58dcdd7a1736aa69a8bc4">CGSCCPassManager</a> &amp;CGPM, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> PipelineText);</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00362" /><CodeLine lineNumber="362"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/passbuilder/#a9ca0e57e6445ab2fe568e53ba29cc0fd">parsePassPipeline</a>(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a613892f4c1a570fd3747f2b6b1bf9b75">LoopPassManager</a> &amp;LPM, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> PipelineText);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00363" /><CodeLine lineNumber="363"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// @&#125;&#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00364" /><CodeLine lineNumber="364"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00365" /><CodeLine lineNumber="365"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Parse a textual MIR pipeline into the provided \\c MachineFunctionPass</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00366" /><CodeLine lineNumber="366"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// manager.</span></CodeLine>
